<section class="legal-page">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="legal-header">
      <h1>Refund & Cancellation Policy</h1>
      <p class="effective-date">Effective Date: October 13, 2025</p>
    </div>

    <div class="legal-content">
      <div class="intro-text">
        <p>At QuantumBayCloud, we want you to be completely satisfied with our services. This Refund & Cancellation Policy explains how we handle refund requests and account cancellations.</p>
      </div>

      <section class="legal-section">
        <h2>1. 30-Day Money-Back Guarantee</h2>
        <p>We offer a 30-day money-back guarantee on all paid plans (Professional and Business). If you're not satisfied with our service, you can request a full refund within 30 days of your initial purchase.</p>
        
        <h3>Eligibility Requirements:</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Refund request must be made within 30 days of the initial purchase date</li>
          <li>Account must not have violated our Terms of Service or Acceptable Use Policy</li>
          <li>Applies only to the first payment of a new subscription</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="legal-section">
        <h2>2. Non-Refundable Items</h2>
        <p>The following items are non-refundable:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Domain Registrations:</strong> Domain name registrations and renewals are non-refundable as they are third-party services</li>
          <li><strong>Setup Fees:</strong> One-time setup or migration fees</li>
          <li><strong>Add-on Services:</strong> Additional storage purchases or premium features</li>
          <li><strong>Services Used Beyond 30 Days:</strong> Renewals or payments made after the initial 30-day period</li>
          <li><strong>Terminated Accounts:</strong> Accounts terminated due to Terms of Service violations</li>
          <li><strong>Partial Month Refunds:</strong> We do not provide prorated refunds for partial months</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="legal-section">
        <h2>3. How to Request a Refund</h2>
        <p>To request a refund:</p>
        <ol>
          <li>Contact our support team at <strong>support@quantumbaycloud.com</strong></li>
          <li>Include your account email address and order number</li>
          <li>Provide a brief reason for the refund request (optional but helps us improve)</li>
          <li>Our team will review your request within 2-3 business days</li>
        </ol>
        
        <h3>Refund Processing Time:</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Approved refunds are processed within 7-10 business days</li>
          <li>Refunds are issued to the original payment method</li>
          <li>Bank processing may take an additional 3-5 business days</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="legal-section">
        <h2>4. Cancellation Policy</h2>
        
        <h3>How to Cancel Your Subscription:</h3>
        <p>You can cancel your subscription at any time:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Log in to your account dashboard</li>
          <li>Go to Billing > Manage Subscription</li>
          <li>Click "Cancel Subscription"</li>
          <li>Confirm cancellation</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>What Happens After Cancellation:</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>You can continue to use the service until the end of your current billing period</li>
          <li>No further charges will be made</li>
          <li>Your account will be downgraded to the Free plan after the billing period ends</li>
          <li>Files exceeding the Free plan storage limit must be deleted or downloaded</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="legal-section">
        <h2>5. Account Deletion</h2>
        <p>If you wish to permanently delete your account:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Cancel your active subscriptions first</li>
          <li>Contact support at <strong>support@quantumbaycloud.com</strong> to request account deletion</li>
          <li>All your data will be permanently deleted within 30 days</li>
          <li>This action cannot be undone</li>
        </ul>
        <p><strong>Important:</strong> Download all important files before requesting account deletion.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="legal-section">
        <h2>6. Downgrades</h2>
        <p>If you downgrade from a paid plan to a lower-tier plan or Free plan:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>The downgrade takes effect at the end of your current billing cycle</li>
          <li>No prorated refunds are provided for downgrades</li>
          <li>You will retain access to paid features until the billing period ends</li>
          <li>Storage exceeding the new plan limit must be managed before downgrade</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="legal-section">
        <h2>7. Upgrades</h2>
        <p>When upgrading your plan:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Upgrades take effect immediately</li>
          <li>You will be charged the prorated difference for the remainder of the billing cycle</li>
          <li>The next billing cycle will charge the full amount of the new plan</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="legal-section">
        <h2>8. Payment Failures</h2>
        <p>If a payment fails:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>We will attempt to process the payment 3 times over 7 days</li>
          <li>You will receive email notifications about the failed payment</li>
          <li>If payment is not resolved, your account may be suspended</li>
          <li>Suspended accounts have 30 days to resolve payment before data deletion</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="legal-section">
        <h2>9. Exceptional Circumstances</h2>
        <p>We may consider refunds outside the standard policy in exceptional circumstances:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Extended service outages beyond our control</li>
          <li>Billing errors on our part</li>
          <li>Technical issues preventing service access</li>
        </ul>
        <p>These are evaluated on a case-by-case basis and require contacting support.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="legal-section">
        <h2>10. Contact Information</h2>
        <p>For refund or cancellation inquiries:</p>
        <p><strong>Email:</strong> support@quantumbaycloud.com<br>
        <strong>Billing Support:</strong> billing@quantumbaycloud.com<br>
        <strong>Response Time:</strong> 24-48 hours</p>
      </section>

      <div class="legal-footer">
        <p>We're committed to providing excellent service. If you have any questions about our refund policy, please don't hesitate to contact us.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

